# Visual tweaks — screenshot before “done”

When you change anything the user **sees** (layout, spacing, alignment, typography, colors, auth/marketing surfaces), **do not** tell them it is finished based on code alone.

## Required check

1. Run or open the relevant screen (local dev server, built preview, or Cursor’s browser preview).
2. **Take at least one screenshot** after the change (browser MCP `browser_take_screenshot`, or the preview’s capture flow).
3. **Look at the image** — edges, alignment, wrapping, contrast — and fix issues you can see there.
4. Only then confirm in chat; if you cannot run the UI, say so and give the smallest manual check instead of asserting it “looks good.”

## Why

CSS/flex intent and what actually renders often diverge (shrink-wrap, percentage bases, wrapping). A screenshot catches that before the user does.

## Exceptions

Skip only for **non-visual** edits (types, APIs, copy in strings without layout change you already verified elsewhere in the same pass).
